node.text:
Hey everyone! It’s @memyselfandsteph_ back again with this fantastical piece for: #MadeWithPhotoshop⁠
⁠
You might have noticed by now that I love to create fantasy, dream-like pieces and this one is no exception. For this pose, I needed to take 3 separate images of myself and then stitched them together via different layers in Photoshop.⁠
⁠
I love creating illusions through my work and this is definitely up there as one of my favourites! It’s always so cool to make someone double-take at your art.⁠
⁠
What’s your favourite style of art? Let me know in the comments. ⁠
⁠
And don’t miss the tap-to-edit of this in the Stories! Thanks, everyone!⁠

node.text:
Hello everyone! @memyselfandsteph_ here’s a little mermaid magic that I #MadeWithPhotoshop⁠
⁠
Finding Photoshop was a real creative game-changer for me. It was the first time I really ever felt like an artist. Photoshop supplied me with all the tools I needed to bring my crazy imagination to life and it blew my mind. ⁠
⁠
Suddenly a world of possibilities was open to me and I poured my heart and soul into creating out-of-this-world pieces that satisfied my weird and wonderful ideas. And for this, I’ll always be grateful to Photoshop.⁠
⁠
How did Photoshop affect your creative journey? Let me know in the comments!⁠
⁠
And don’t forget to head over to Photoshop’s stories to see the tap-to-edit of this piece!⁠

Hi! My name is Kate and today I would like to share with you my new art for #MadeWithPhotoshop ⁠
⁠
I love creating environmental art. I love to imagine new colorful worlds with beautiful places and amazing things. These worlds are not always very different from Earth, but there’s always something unique about them that inspires me, and I hope it inspires you too!⁠
⁠
I want to see what you #MadeWithPhotoshop 💙⁠
